## Context

The backend IS generating Claude responses — server logs show `[mira] AGENT SAID: ...` with full text. But the frontend plays no voice and shows no avatar lip sync. The browser console shows zero `mira_speech`-related logs.

## Root cause: `!data.text` guard kills end-of-message signal

**File:** `frontend/src/app/mirror/page.tsx`, line 128

```
handleSpeech(data):
  if (!data.text) return;          ← LINE 128: "" is falsy in JS → exits!
  if (data.is_chunk !== false) {
    // accumulate chunk
  } else {
    // end-of-message: flush to TTS  ← NEVER REACHED
  }
```

The backend sends two kinds of `mira_speech` events:
- **Chunks**: `{"text": "some words", "is_chunk": true}` — these pass the guard fine
- **End-of-message**: `{"text": "", "is_chunk": false}` — empty string is falsy in JS, so `!data.text` is `true` → handler returns early

The chunks accumulate silently in `responseAccumulatorRef`, but the end-of-message signal that triggers `sentenceBuffer.feed()` → TTS → avatar is **completely dropped**. The accumulated text is never flushed.

## Fix

### 1. `frontend/src/app/mirror/page.tsx` — Fix the guard logic

Move the `!data.text` check inside the chunk branch only. The end-of-message branch must always execute regardless of whether `text` is empty:

```typescript
if (data.is_chunk !== false) {
  // Still accumulating chunks
  if (!data.text) return;  // Skip empty chunks (no-ops)
  responseAccumulatorRef.current += data.text;
  avatar.setAvatarState("thinking");
} else {
  // End of message — flush accumulated text to TTS
  if (data.text) {
    responseAccumulatorRef.current += data.text;
  }
  const fullText = responseAccumulatorRef.current;
  responseAccumulatorRef.current = "";
  console.log("[Mirror] Agent full response:", fullText);
  // ... scripted response check, sentence buffer, TTS
}
```

Also add a log when chunks arrive so we can confirm socket events are reaching the frontend:
```typescript
console.log("[Mirror] mira_speech chunk:", data.text?.slice(0, 60));
```

### 2. `backend/agent/orchestrator.py` — Minor: add logging at silent returns

Add `print()` statements at the two silent early-return points in `handle_event()` so we can diagnose future issues:
- Session not found (`self.sessions.get(user_id)` returns None)
- `_call_claude` API limit / tool depth reached

Also emit a fallback error message to the frontend when Claude API fails (currently only logged server-side).

### Files to modify

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `frontend/src/app/mirror/page.tsx` | Fix `!data.text` guard (line 128), add chunk arrival logging |
| `backend/agent/orchestrator.py` | Add logging at silent returns, emit fallback on Claude API failure |

## Verification

1. `cd frontend && npx tsc --noEmit` — no type errors
2. Start backend + frontend, open `/mirror?user_id=...`, click Start Session
3. Backend logs: `[mira] AGENT SAID: ...` (already working)
4. Frontend console should now show:
   - `[Mirror] mira_speech chunk: ...` — for each streamed chunk
   - `[Mirror] Agent full response: ...` — when end-of-message fires
   - `[SentenceBuffer] Sentence: ...` — per-sentence TTS
   - `[TTS] Sending to ElevenLabs: ...` — TTS proxy call
5. Audio plays through speakers, avatar switches to talking state

